WEBVTT

01:19.601 --> 01:21.298
♪ THERE ARE TIMES

01:21.342 --> 01:24.432
♪ WHEN I SIT ALONE

01:24.475 --> 01:29.480
♪ PULLING MYSELF
AWAY FROM THE UNKNOWN ♪

01:29.524 --> 01:34.355
♪ PATTERNS OF LIFE
OF WHAT WE SEE AND FEEL ♪

01:34.398 --> 01:39.664
♪ ON THE OTHER SIDE
KNOWING WHAT IS REAL ♪

01:39.708 --> 01:44.713
♪ MY OTHER SELF
I AM TRYING TO HIDE ♪

01:44.756 --> 01:47.455
♪ FORBIDDEN DOORS

01:47.498 --> 01:53.025
♪ ON THE OTHER SIDE

02:17.093 --> 02:19.878
♪ ON THE OTHER

02:19.922 --> 02:23.708
♪ SIDE ♪

02:43.554 --> 02:46.383
[ Woman ]
YOU'RE TAKING ON AN AWFUL LOT
WITH THIS GIRL, HENRY.

02:46.427 --> 02:49.081
SHE DESERVES A CHANCE
ON THE OUTSIDE, AMANDA.

02:49.125 --> 02:51.780
BUT, UNFORTUNATELY, HER PARENTS
WANT NOTHING TO DO WITH HER.

02:51.823 --> 02:54.086
THE CLUB IS PERFECT.
IT'S A CONTROLLED ENVIRONMENT.

02:54.130 --> 02:56.132
SHE'LL HAVE A JOB,
A PLACE TO LIVE.

02:56.176 --> 02:57.655
WHAT IF SHE DEVELOPS
ANOTHER OBSESSION?

02:57.699 --> 02:59.701
I'M TELLIN' YOU
THAT'S NOT GOING TO HAPPEN.

02:59.744 --> 03:01.485
I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT,
FOR YOUR SAKE.

03:01.529 --> 03:04.575
BECAUSE YOU AND I BOTH KNOW THAT
THIS PROGRESS COULD BE NOTHING

03:04.619 --> 03:06.273
MORE THAN AN ELABORATE MASK.

03:06.316 --> 03:09.493
AMANDA, I KNOW I'M RIGHT
ABOUT THIS GIRL. I KNOW IT.

03:09.537 --> 03:14.281
YOU KNOW THE RULES. IF SHE
PUTS ONE FOOT OVER THE LINE,
SHE'S BACK IN THE WARD.

03:18.285 --> 03:20.069
GOOD LUCK.

03:28.904 --> 03:31.385
TANYA, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING IN MY ROOM?[ Gasps ]

03:33.561 --> 03:35.737
DID YOU COME
TO SAY GOOD-BYE?

03:37.391 --> 03:39.784
NO!
[ Screams ]

03:42.047 --> 03:44.789
WHAT?

03:44.833 --> 03:48.271
-DID YOU WANT THIS?
-WHAT DO YOU
NEED 'EM FOR?

03:50.012 --> 03:52.971
I MEAN, YOU'RE LEAVING,
SO WHY CAN'T I--THAT'S RIGHT.

03:53.015 --> 03:55.365
I'M LEAVING
AND YOU'RE STAYING.

03:59.326 --> 04:01.241
LEAVE IT!

04:03.808 --> 04:09.553
YOU'RE CRAZY. THEY'RE GONNA SEE
IT ON YOU OUT THERE.

04:09.597 --> 04:13.035
THEY'RE GONNA SEE IT
ALL OVER YOU.

04:15.037 --> 04:18.692
AND THEY'LL SEND YOU BACK.

04:18.736 --> 04:20.695
YOU'LL SEE.

04:20.738 --> 04:23.828
THEY'LL SEND YOU BACK.

04:23.872 --> 04:26.396
THEY'LL SEND YOU BACK!

04:26.440 --> 04:29.791
THEY'LL BRING YOU BACK!
[ Laughing ]

04:29.834 --> 04:32.576
THEY'LL BRING YOU BACK!

04:40.323 --> 04:42.804
[ Girl ]
YOU KNOW, DOC, WE STILL
HAVEN'T HAD THAT TALK...

04:42.847 --> 04:46.329
ABOUT THIS WHOLE
"KNOCKING A LITTLE BALL INTO
A HOLE" OBSESSION OF YOURS.

04:46.373 --> 04:48.853
LOOK, I LIKE TO HEAR YOU
JOKING AND ALL, ALRIGHT?

04:48.897 --> 04:51.639
BUT PLEASE I NEED TO KNOW THAT
YOU'RE TAKING THIS SERIOUSLY.

04:51.682 --> 04:53.728
-I KNOW THE RULES.
-TELL ME.

04:53.771 --> 04:57.340
NO DRUGS, NO DRINKING,
NO LEAVING LANG COUNTY.

04:57.384 --> 05:00.256
AND IF I GET FIRED--YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO GET FIRED.

05:02.040 --> 05:04.391
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

05:04.434 --> 05:08.264
♪ WHEN THERE'S NO ONE LEFT
TO TAKE YOU BY THE HAND ♪

05:08.308 --> 05:12.181
♪ AND SAY IT'S OKAY
WE UNDERSTAND ♪

05:12.224 --> 05:15.053
♪ WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES

05:17.055 --> 05:21.538
♪ INSTEAD THEY BEAT YOU DOWN AND
SAY THAT IT'S OKAY TO DROWN ♪

05:21.582 --> 05:24.541
♪ JUST HOLD YOUR BREATH
BE STRONG ♪THANKS.

05:24.585 --> 05:30.808
♪ JUST TAKE YOUR TIME
AND YOU'LL BE FINE ♪

05:30.852 --> 05:35.378
-DO THEY KNOW ABOUT ME?
-YOU'RE A FRIEND OF THE FAMILY'S
WHO NEEDS A JOB FOR THE SUMMER.

05:35.422 --> 05:39.295
THAT'S ALL I TOLD THEM.
THAT'S ALL THEY NEED TO KNOW.

05:39.339 --> 05:41.950
COME ON.
IT'S FINE. COME ON.

05:49.305 --> 05:50.567
WHO IS THAT?

05:50.611 --> 05:55.180
♪ OH, I DON'T KNOW HOW TO

05:55.224 --> 05:58.183
♪ STAY ALIVE ♪

06:00.447 --> 06:02.753
<i>I HAVEN'T PLAYED IN MONTHS.</i>

06:02.797 --> 06:06.540
FORGET IT.
YOU'RE NOT IN MY LEAGUE.

06:06.583 --> 06:10.195
-SO, YOU'RE ADRIEN.
-THIS IS BOB MEAD,
CLUB MANAGER.

06:10.239 --> 06:12.720
I HOPE YOU'RE PREPARED
TO WORK VERY HARD.

06:12.763 --> 06:14.896
-I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO IT.
-GOOD.

06:14.939 --> 06:18.247
JUST REMEMBER YOUR PLACE
AND YOU'LL DO FINE.

06:18.290 --> 06:20.858
WHY DON'T WE, UH,
GO FIND JOANNE?

06:22.773 --> 06:27.474
MEAD'S NOT SO BAD. BEST THING
IS JUST TO STAY OUT OF HIS WAY.

06:27.517 --> 06:31.565
IF HE THINKS YOU'RE LIKE
DISSING HIM, HE CAN MAKE
YOUR LIFE HERE REAL DARK.

06:32.740 --> 06:34.306
THANKS.

06:36.091 --> 06:39.616
<i>LISTEN, BOBBY, UH, TRY NOT
TO CROWD HER TOO MUCH.</i>

06:39.660 --> 06:43.228
<i>BUT IF YOU SEE ANYTHING
THAT STRIKES YOU AS WORRISOME,</i>

06:43.272 --> 06:46.449
LET ME KNOW BEFORE
ANYBODY ELSE, OKAY?

06:46.493 --> 06:47.668
SURE.

06:51.976 --> 06:55.371
YEAH, WELL,
THIS IS MY THIRD SEASON.

06:55.415 --> 06:58.983
AND LAST YEAR, I WORKED SO HARD,
LIKE EVERY SHIFT.

06:59.027 --> 07:02.247
BUT MADE ENOUGH MONEY
TO BUY MY TRUCK.

07:02.291 --> 07:06.948
YOU PUT IN THE TIME,
IT'S NOT SO BAD SO LONG AS
YOU HAVE SOMETHING TO WORK FOR.

07:06.991 --> 07:09.516
<i>SO, WHAT ABOUT YOU?</i>

07:09.559 --> 07:14.303
I DON'T KNOW. I MEAN, I DON'T
HAVE, LIKE, PLANS OR ANYTHING.

07:14.346 --> 07:17.262
YOU GOT TO.
I MEAN, YOU GOT TO,

07:17.306 --> 07:19.395
YOU KNOW,
TO GET THROUGH.

07:22.833 --> 07:25.183
HANG ON!
HANG ON!

07:28.926 --> 07:32.539
ALL YOU GOT TO REMEMBER TO GET
BY IS JUST BE INVISIBLE.

07:32.582 --> 07:35.846
THAT'S WHAT I DO.
AND COUNT YOUR MONEY.

07:38.327 --> 07:40.460
[ Girl ]
GREG, YOU'RE A BASTARD!

07:40.503 --> 07:43.245
WILL YOU GRAB
AN END THERE?

07:43.288 --> 07:46.988
THEY GET ALL PISSY AND SHIT
IF YOU LET IT TOUCH THE GROUND.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.995
IF YOU JUST LET IT DOWN,
I'LL GET THE...

07:54.038 --> 07:56.084
I DON'T KNOW.

07:58.042 --> 08:00.567
OH, YEAH.

08:00.610 --> 08:02.438
YOU'LL GET PLENTY
OF THEM THIS SUMMER.

08:02.482 --> 08:05.702
<i>THE ROYAL SWINE
IS WHAT WE CALL THEM.</i>

08:05.746 --> 08:08.618
THEY ALL THINK
THEY'RE GOD'S GIFT.

08:08.662 --> 08:11.926
<i>THE BLONDE BOMBSHELL,
THAT'S SHEILA.</i>

08:11.969 --> 08:16.017
BUT THE LUSCIOUS BRUNETTE
IS BRITTANY FOSTER.

08:16.060 --> 08:18.236
SHE'S THE QUEEN.

08:24.112 --> 08:26.462
MAYBE IN MY NEXT LIFE.

08:28.246 --> 08:30.771
[ Joanne ]
IT'S NOT A LIFE.

08:30.814 --> 08:32.903
IT'S A J. CREW CATALOGUE.

09:03.978 --> 09:05.719
[ Door Opens ]

09:07.329 --> 09:10.375
- JESUS!
- MEAD TOLD ME
TO BRING THIS TO YOU.

09:12.987 --> 09:16.947
YOU KNOW, NEXT TIME
-YOU COULD TRY KNOCKING.
-I'M SORRY.

09:16.991 --> 09:20.647
IT'S JUST THAT
YOUR DOOR WAS OPEN
AND I THOUGHT--

09:20.690 --> 09:24.694
WELL, UM, IT'S JUST
YOU AND ME ON THIS FLOOR.

09:27.436 --> 09:31.483
-I'M WAYNE.
-ADRIEN.

09:31.527 --> 09:33.007
I KNOW.

09:48.762 --> 09:51.199
[ Laughing ]
HUH?

09:51.242 --> 09:53.114
-WHO'S THE MAN?
-AH!

09:53.157 --> 09:56.770
THE CLASSICS NEVER GROW OLD.
OR DON'T THEY?

09:56.813 --> 09:58.598
JUST LIKE YOU, BOYS.

09:58.641 --> 10:00.904
[ Girl ]
-HEY, WHAT'S IN THE BAG?
-BE COOL, ALRIGHT?

10:00.948 --> 10:03.428
AREN'T YOU GUYS GETTING
A LITTLE OLD FOR THIS?

10:03.472 --> 10:05.953
THEY WERE GETTING TOO OLD
FOR IT FIVE YEARS AGO.

10:05.996 --> 10:07.302
[ Giggling ][ Growling ]

10:09.434 --> 10:10.914
-HEY.
-HEY, SHEILA.

10:10.958 --> 10:12.089
ONE OF YOU BRAINIACS.

10:12.133 --> 10:15.615
- WHAT?
- GREEK GODDESS OF THE HUNT.

10:15.658 --> 10:17.094
SEVEN LETTERS.

10:23.144 --> 10:24.493
HEY.

10:26.234 --> 10:27.670
<i>WELL, WELL.</i>

10:27.714 --> 10:28.976
HI.

10:34.285 --> 10:37.375
- SHH, SHH. <i>
- OH, NO. OH, MY GOD.</i>

10:37.419 --> 10:38.855
[ Man ]
I WANNA GO BACK OUT.

10:40.857 --> 10:44.556
COME ON, PEOPLE.
-GREEK GODDESS OF THE HUNT.
-SHH.

10:44.600 --> 10:45.949
THAT'S EASY.
DIANA.

10:51.738 --> 10:54.436
IT'S, UM, ARTEMIS.

10:56.786 --> 11:00.398
GREEK GODDESS OF THE HUNT.
ARTEMIS.

11:00.442 --> 11:02.226
DIANA WAS THE ROMAN ONE.

11:09.756 --> 11:12.367
<i>BOYS, I THINK
YOU MET YOUR MATCH.</i>

11:12.410 --> 11:17.067
DID WE JUST GET DISSED
-BY THE CABANA GIRL?
-GOD, YOU'RE QUICK.

11:17.111 --> 11:18.895
<i>WHAT'S GOING ON,
BRITTANY? HEY, SEXY.</i>

11:18.939 --> 11:20.810
<i>HEY, BRIT. HELLO.</i>

11:20.854 --> 11:22.638
DID YOU JUST SEE
THE NEW GIRL?

11:22.682 --> 11:25.946
THE FIRST TIME I SAW HER
I SWEAR I THOUGHT IT WAS SANDRA.

11:25.989 --> 11:27.251
SHE'S GOT THAT SAME--

11:29.863 --> 11:31.429
DON'T YOU THINK?

11:34.041 --> 11:35.477
YEAH.

11:55.758 --> 11:58.718
<i>- [ Adrien ]
OH, GOD!
- SHIT!</i>

11:58.761 --> 12:01.677
- I'M-- I'M SORRY.
- SANDRA?

12:01.721 --> 12:05.855
- ARE YOU ALRIGHT?
- YEAH, JUST A FEW FINGERS.

12:05.899 --> 12:11.382
THIS IS THE THIRD TIME
THIS MONTH. THINK SHE'S
TRYING TO TELL ME SOMETHING?

12:11.426 --> 12:14.168
I THINK SHE THINKS
YOU'RE READY TO START
PLAYING REAL PEOPLE.

12:14.211 --> 12:16.736
OH, NO, NO.
I GET THAT ALL DAY LONG.[ Laughing ]

12:16.779 --> 12:18.868
BERTHA HERE ALWAYS
GETS IT OVER THE NET.

12:18.912 --> 12:22.480
SHE NEVER COMPLAINS
ABOUT THE HUSBAND WORKING LATE
OR THE KIDS WRECKING THE CAR--

12:22.524 --> 12:25.005
OR SHOWS UP LATE
FOR HER APPOINTMENT?

12:25.048 --> 12:27.355
SORRY. I JUST COULDN'T GET
MOTIVATED THIS MORNING.

12:27.398 --> 12:30.445
AND HOW DOES THAT MAKE
THIS MORNING ANY DIFFERENT
FROM ANY OTHER?

12:30.488 --> 12:32.360
PLEASE DON'T BE
SO OBVIOUS.

12:32.403 --> 12:35.885
MATT'S JUST TRYING
TO IMPRESS YOU WITH
HIS TOUGH LOVE COACHING STYLE.

12:35.929 --> 12:38.279
BRITTANY'S JUST TERRIFIED
THAT IF SHE ACTUALLY APPLIED
HERSELF...

12:38.322 --> 12:41.804
SHE COULD BE ONE OF THE BETTER
PLAYERS AT THE CLUB.

12:41.848 --> 12:45.634
- SO YOU'RE NEW HERE, HUH?
- YEAH, IT'S MY FIRST DAY.

12:45.677 --> 12:49.899
WELL, DON'T WORRY. MATT'S BEEN
HERE FOR WHAT, FIVE YEARS?

12:49.943 --> 12:54.164
- SIX.
- SEE? AND THEY STILL
HAVEN'T FIRED HIM YET.

12:54.208 --> 12:57.951
WHO KNOWS? BY THE END
OF THE SUMMER,
YOU COULD BE RUNNING THIS PLACE.

13:05.523 --> 13:07.830
HEY, JUST REMEMBER.

13:07.874 --> 13:10.267
IT'S ALL ABOUT THE TIPS.
YOU'LL DO FINE.

13:12.922 --> 13:14.315
SHOW TIME.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.361
<i>OH, NO, WAIT,
ARE YOU SERIOUS?</i>

13:20.930 --> 13:22.279
CASH MONEY, CASH MONEY.

13:22.323 --> 13:23.846
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

13:23.890 --> 13:27.023
<i>HOW MUCH
DID DADDY GIVE YOU? JUST TEN.</i>

13:27.067 --> 13:31.201
<i>[ Sheila ]
TEN THOUSAND DOLLARS. HEY!</i>

13:31.245 --> 13:33.334
- HEY, TOM.
- TOM. - TOM.

13:33.377 --> 13:35.075
YOU GUYS JONESING
FOR SOME GOLF?

13:35.118 --> 13:36.859
YOU LOOK GOOD.

13:36.903 --> 13:40.602
JUST IN TIME. I'M SO THIRSTY
I COULD DRINK A GLASS OF WATER.

13:40.645 --> 13:42.560
OOH, LOOK.
TWINS.

13:59.316 --> 14:02.015
-HELLO, DOCTOR.
-HELLO, BRITTANY.

14:10.458 --> 14:13.635
-WHERE YOU BEEN, MAN?
-BEEN OUT. JUST... ON VACATION.

14:13.678 --> 14:17.378
I THOUGHT YOU
-WERE IN REHAB.
-DING-DING.

14:17.421 --> 14:20.033
-WHAT'S UP?
-HEY, BRIT.

14:20.076 --> 14:23.732
WHAT IS THIS,
A FUNERAL OR A PARTY?

14:23.775 --> 14:25.342
JUST A LITTLE THOUGHT
IN PASSING.

14:25.386 --> 14:28.215
I THINK YOU'RE A LITTLE MORE FUN
WHEN YOU'RE DOING BLOW.

14:28.258 --> 14:30.217
GREG, FIGURES.

14:30.260 --> 14:32.784
LET'S GET A DRINK.
LET'S CELEBRATE.
LET'S GET SAUCED UP.

14:32.828 --> 14:34.830
THIS IS MY FIRST NIGHT OUT.
COME ON

14:34.874 --> 14:37.789
WHOA, WHOA. THEN, WE SHOULD
CELEBRATE, SHOULDN'T WE?

14:46.059 --> 14:49.801
WHOA.

14:49.845 --> 14:52.108
WHERE DID YOU
COME FROM?

14:52.152 --> 14:56.025
WELL, UH, I WAS--
I WAS ACTUALLY AT THE BAR.

14:56.069 --> 14:59.899
-YES?
-AND I--
I WAS MINDING MY OWN BUSINESS.

14:59.942 --> 15:03.511
AND THEN, I HEARD THIS VOICE
COMING UP FROM BEHIND THE BAR.

15:03.554 --> 15:06.644
IT WAS LIKE--
[ High-Pitched Voice ]
"KELLY!

15:08.472 --> 15:10.866
"KELLY,

15:10.910 --> 15:12.955
DRINK ME."

15:12.999 --> 15:16.785
THEY SEEMED TO KNOW YOU,
SO I HAD TO BRING THEM
TO YOU RIGHT AWAY.

15:16.828 --> 15:19.657
YOU SURE IT WASN'T
YOUR NAME THAT THEY
WERE CALLING, BOBBY?

15:19.701 --> 15:23.270
YOU'RE RIGHT.
WE SHOULD DRINK THEM TOGETHER.

15:23.313 --> 15:25.228
I THINK I'LL PASS.

15:27.013 --> 15:28.579
WAIT...

15:28.623 --> 15:31.234
[ Bottles Dropping ]

15:32.888 --> 15:35.108
REMEMBER THE LAST SUMMER...

15:35.151 --> 15:38.024
WHEN WE WENT OUT-- <i>WHEN WE GOT STUCK
IN THE SANDBAR...</i>

15:38.067 --> 15:41.549
BECAUSE YOU DECIDED
TO CUT THE MARKER?

15:41.592 --> 15:44.247
BUT THAT WASN'T
SO BAD, WAS IT?

15:55.476 --> 15:57.391
THAT WAS LAST SUMMER.

16:10.186 --> 16:12.101
HEY.

16:12.145 --> 16:13.885
♪ [ Techno Pop ]

16:16.932 --> 16:19.239
♪

16:25.201 --> 16:28.900
YOU DIDN'T HEAR?
HIS PARENTS BOUGHT HIM
A BRAND-NEW HUMMER.

16:28.944 --> 16:32.339
JUST FOR MAKING IT
-THROUGH REHAB?
-OH, MY GOD.

16:32.382 --> 16:36.473
THE AMOUNT OF MONEY
HE WAS STUFFING UP HIS NOSE,
THEY'RE GETTING A GOOD DEAL.

16:36.517 --> 16:39.346
OKAY, NOW I HAVE IT. <i>THE SECOND
HE SCREWS UP,</i>

16:39.389 --> 16:42.827
THE CAR IS BACK
TO THE DEALERSHIP.

16:42.871 --> 16:44.220
BRIT, YOU OKAY?

16:45.917 --> 16:48.137
YEAH, I'M FINE.
I JUST HAVE A HEADACHE.

16:48.181 --> 16:50.270
<i>I DON'T CARE.
I THINK IT'S GOOD.</i>

16:50.313 --> 16:52.794
<i>YEAH, DON'T YOU?</i>

16:52.837 --> 16:55.057
THE ICE MACHINE IS BROKEN.
GRAB A BUS BOX.

16:55.101 --> 16:58.147
GO TO THE POOL AND BRING
SOME ICE TO THE SERVICE BAR.

16:58.191 --> 16:59.757
JOANNE WILL COVER
YOUR TABLES.

17:18.646 --> 17:20.430
[ Water Splashing ]

17:46.500 --> 17:48.241
OH, MY GOD.
[ Drops Bucket ]

18:13.701 --> 18:15.746
COME ON. BREATHE.

18:17.531 --> 18:19.402
COME ON.

18:31.153 --> 18:33.024
YOU OKAY?

18:35.984 --> 18:38.378
I FEEL SO STUPID.

18:38.421 --> 18:41.120
I JUST WANTED
TO COOL MY FEET OFF.

18:42.121 --> 18:44.210
AND THEN, WELL...

18:46.429 --> 18:49.128
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

18:58.137 --> 19:00.878
TRY THIS.

19:00.922 --> 19:02.619
I LOVE THIS PAINTING.

19:04.273 --> 19:08.277
-YEAH.
-IT'S ALMOST AS IF SHE
LEFT SOMETHING BEHIND.

19:10.105 --> 19:13.108
SOMETHING SHE KNOWS
SHE CAN NEVER GO BACK FOR.

19:16.459 --> 19:20.507
ADRIEN! DO YOU THINK
I'M PLAYING A GAME WITH YOU?
I ASKED YOU 20 MINUTES AGO...

19:20.550 --> 19:22.552
TO GET ME--

19:22.596 --> 19:26.034
IS THERE A PROBLEM HERE?

19:26.077 --> 19:27.949
MISS FOSTER.

19:27.992 --> 19:30.169
NO.

19:32.171 --> 19:35.652
I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T, UH--
EXCUSE ME.

19:38.351 --> 19:40.309
[ Laughing ]

19:55.324 --> 19:57.021
[ Rumbling ]

20:09.164 --> 20:11.427
[ Greg ]
I HOPE SHE HAS
ENOUGH OXYGEN IN THERE.

20:13.168 --> 20:14.909
[ Whirring ]

20:18.869 --> 20:20.741
[ Elevator Bell Rings ]

20:22.743 --> 20:26.616
-GOING UP?
-I WOULDN'T. I ALMOST
GOT STUCK IN THIS THING.

20:26.660 --> 20:29.315
IT WAS THE BREAKER BOX.
SOMEBODY'S IDEA OF A JOKE.

20:30.751 --> 20:33.536
CUTE.

20:33.580 --> 20:35.146
I WOULDN'T TAKE IT
TOO PERSONALLY.

20:35.190 --> 20:38.019
AFTER ALL,
YOU ARE <i>THE NEW GIRL.</i>

20:38.062 --> 20:41.240
IS THAT WHO I AM?

20:41.283 --> 20:44.025
I'M AFRAID SO.

20:44.068 --> 20:45.592
[ Elevator Bell Rings ]

20:45.635 --> 20:50.031
WELL, THANKS
-FOR SAVING MY LIFE.
-SAVING YOUR LIFE?

20:50.074 --> 20:55.166
- WHAT DID I MISS?
- OH, HEY, NOTHING.
THE ELEVATOR GOT STUCK IS ALL.

20:55.210 --> 20:57.734
AND LET ME GUESS.
MATT CAME TO YOUR RESCUE.

20:57.778 --> 21:00.650
IT WAS SOMEBODY'S
-IDEA OF A JOKE.
-OH.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.001
HA HA.

21:04.045 --> 21:07.875
UM, YOU TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.
I GUESS I'LL SEE YOU IN AN HOUR.

21:07.918 --> 21:11.270
-MAYBE.
-EXCUSE ME.

21:15.665 --> 21:18.842
SOMEBODY HAS A THING
FOR THE TENNIS PRO.

21:18.886 --> 21:21.845
IT'S NOT JUST A THING.

21:21.889 --> 21:26.459
<i>LISTEN, I KNOW IT'S SHORT
NOTICE, BUT I'M HAVING A PARTY
TONIGHT ON THE BEACH.</i>

21:28.591 --> 21:33.379
IT'S NOTHING BIG,
BUT I WOULD REALLY
LIKE FOR YOU TO COME.

21:33.422 --> 21:36.860
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THAT.

21:36.904 --> 21:42.779
SAY YOU'LL COME.
I HAVE A REAL PROBLEM
DEALING WITH REJECTION.

21:42.823 --> 21:46.740
OKAY. I MEAN,
I HAVE TO CHECK MY--EXCELLENT.

21:46.783 --> 21:49.220
THEN, I'LL SEE YOU
TONIGHT.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.136
YEAH.

21:54.356 --> 21:57.185
BRITTANY, COME ON.
LET'S GO. I'M WAITING.

