31:00.293 --> 31:03.862
- YOU DID NOT JUST SAY THAT.
- NO, SERIOUSLY.
IT'S CALLED YOUR STANCE.

31:03.905 --> 31:05.689
LET ME SHOW YOU.

31:05.733 --> 31:10.303
NOW, THE STANCE HAS TO DO WITH
THE POSITIONING OF YOUR LEGS.

31:10.346 --> 31:12.609
SO WE'RE GONNA PULL THESE OUT.
THERE WE GO.

31:12.653 --> 31:15.569
HIPS ROLLED IN.
-JUST LIKE THAT.
-UH-HUH.

31:15.612 --> 31:18.572
OH, YES. YOU KNEW THAT ONE.
SHOULDERS RELAXED.

31:18.615 --> 31:20.748
JUST LIKE THAT.

31:20.791 --> 31:23.403
GO AHEAD.
GIVE IT A TRY.

31:23.446 --> 31:25.709
HE'S PRACTICALLY
ON HIS KNEES.

31:31.106 --> 31:34.109
NOT BAD, KID. NOT BAD.[ Chuckling ]

31:34.153 --> 31:37.939
THINGS COULDN'T HAVE
WORKED OUT BETTER
IF SOMEBODY PLANNED IT.

31:37.983 --> 31:40.855
<i>[ Brittany ]
KEL, YOU'RE UP.</i>

32:00.875 --> 32:03.008
[ Tom ]
DO YOU WANNA PLAY
AGAIN THIS WEEKEND?

32:03.051 --> 32:07.577
<i>YEAH, I WOULD LOVE TO.
I'M JUST GONNA HAVE
TO SEE ABOUT MY SCHEDULE.</i>

32:07.621 --> 32:09.579
GOOD DEAL.

32:12.104 --> 32:16.108
NO, IT'S BACK A LITTLE,
ABOUT, UH, 15 FEET IN.

32:18.675 --> 32:21.983
[ Kelly ]
FORGET IT.
IT'S-- IT'S LOST.

32:22.027 --> 32:26.988
NO, IT'S-- IT'S RIGHT THERE.
-JUST BACK A LITTLE.
-I'LL JUST TAKE A DROP.

32:27.032 --> 32:29.077
-I'M SURE I SAW IT.
-JUST FORGET IT.

32:29.121 --> 32:31.862
<i>ADRIEN,
LET HER TAKE THE DROP.</i>

32:37.738 --> 32:39.740
YOU ARE SO LUCKY.

32:39.783 --> 32:43.396
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO GET TOM
TO GIVE ME POINTERS FOR YEARS.

32:44.963 --> 32:48.749
YEAH, AND HE'S GOT
SOME POINTERS, ALRIGHT.

32:48.792 --> 32:52.883
COME ON. YOU CAN'T SAY
YOU HATED THAT. I SAW YOU.

32:52.927 --> 32:55.147
[ Both Laughing ]

33:01.588 --> 33:05.374
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT
YOU KNEW DR. THOMPSON.

33:08.203 --> 33:11.641
YEAH. YEAH.
HE'S A FRIEND OF THE FAMILY.

33:11.685 --> 33:14.818
HE'S ACTUALLY THE ONE
THAT GOT ME THIS JOB.

33:14.862 --> 33:18.126
IT'S OKAY, ADRIEN.
I KNOW.

33:20.607 --> 33:27.048
LOOK, IT'S NO BIGGIE.
SO, YOU WERE IN, UM,
SAINT ANASTASIA.

33:27.092 --> 33:30.486
TRUST ME. HALF THE PEOPLE
AROUND HERE HAVE BEEN
IN REHAB OR THERAPY.

33:30.530 --> 33:34.055
AND IF THEY HAVEN'T,
THEY SHOULD BE.

33:34.099 --> 33:38.277
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU THOUGHT YOU'D NEED
TO PUT ON A SHOW WITH ME.

33:38.320 --> 33:40.844
I MEAN,
WE ARE FRIENDS, RIGHT?

33:42.890 --> 33:44.805
YEAH.

33:46.546 --> 33:48.896
YEAH.

33:48.939 --> 33:52.639
YOU KNOW, WHY DON'T YOU, UM,
HANG ON TO THOSE CLUBS?

33:55.120 --> 33:58.558
THANKS.

33:58.601 --> 34:00.777
TOM'S ON THE GOLF COURSE
ALMOST EVERY DAY,

34:00.821 --> 34:03.432
AND HE'S ALWAYS LOOKING
FOR SOMEONE TO PLAY WITH.

34:06.305 --> 34:08.524
[ Sighs ] OH!

34:30.242 --> 34:32.809
[ Door Creaking ]

34:37.161 --> 34:39.599
[ Creaking Continues ]

34:56.790 --> 34:58.705
[ Creaking ][ Gasps ]

35:37.091 --> 35:39.180
OH!

35:41.139 --> 35:42.444
OH.

35:57.285 --> 36:00.070
[ Man ]
THANKS. HAVE A NICE EVENING.

36:10.472 --> 36:12.387
[ Doorbell Rings ]

36:18.480 --> 36:20.308
[ Ringing ]

36:23.964 --> 36:26.227
HELLO?

36:58.781 --> 37:00.740
BRITTANY?

37:36.558 --> 37:39.344
[ Brittany ]
I TOLD YOU
YOU'D KILL IN THAT DRESS.

37:41.694 --> 37:45.959
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU.
I ALMOST...

37:46.002 --> 37:48.788
JUST FOR A SECOND--LET ME GUESS.

37:48.831 --> 37:51.051
YOU ALMOST DIDN'T
ACCEPT IT.

37:51.094 --> 37:53.053
AND THEN YOU PUT IT ON--

37:53.096 --> 37:57.797
AND THERE WAS NO WAY
I WAS GIVING IT BACK.

38:00.582 --> 38:02.715
[ Guests Chattering ]

38:06.806 --> 38:11.376
SO, WHAT'S THE DEAL?
IF YOU MISS, YOUR GIRLFRIEND
SUCKS MY DUCK FOR FREE.

38:11.419 --> 38:13.334
[ Morgan ] DON'T CHOKE, ANDY.

38:13.378 --> 38:17.556
MORGAN, THIS IS SICK.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS
JUST 'CAUSE HE SAID.

38:17.599 --> 38:20.646
DON'T I?

38:20.689 --> 38:25.912
ALRIGHT, EASY, PAL.
FINE, BUT THE THOUSAND
DOLLARS STILL STICKS.

38:32.788 --> 38:34.703
RIGHT THERE. OH, YES.

38:34.747 --> 38:37.097
WHAT'S THE MATTER, KELLY?
YOU LOOK A LITTLE GREEN.

38:37.140 --> 38:41.710
- BOBBY, ADRIEN NEEDS A DRINK.
- OH, DOES--

38:41.754 --> 38:44.322
<i>ADRIEN? YOU LOOK GREAT.</i>

38:44.365 --> 38:47.499
<i>BOBBY! YOUR ONE
PURPOSE ON THIS PLANET--</i>

38:47.542 --> 38:50.153
IS MAKING ME
A DRINK.

38:51.503 --> 38:53.983
CAREFUL.
THIS ONE LEARNS FAST.

38:57.422 --> 39:00.338
WHERE HAVE YOU GUYS BEEN,
UPSTAIRS THIS WHOLE TIME?

39:00.381 --> 39:04.646
I MEAN,
WE'RE ALL OUT...

39:04.690 --> 39:06.344
HERE.

39:06.387 --> 39:08.737
SO, I'M GONNA MAKE YOU
ONE OF MY FAVORITES.

39:08.781 --> 39:11.305
ACTUALLY,
THEY'RE ALL MY FAVORITES,
SO THAT PRESENTS A PROBLEM.

39:11.349 --> 39:15.396
SO, WHY DON'T WE JUST NARROW IT
DOWN TO THE CLASSICS,
WHICH WOULD BE A MARTINI.

39:15.440 --> 39:18.138
<i>WHAT?
SHUT UP! LOSER!</i>

39:22.098 --> 39:26.146
- WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
LOOKING AT, CARL?
- WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?

39:27.452 --> 39:30.411
COME HERE WITH ME,
LITTLE TROPHY CUP.

39:30.455 --> 39:35.460
WELL, IF YOU WANNA KNOW,
ANDY WAS A LITTLE SHORT
OF CASH THIS WEEKEND...

39:35.503 --> 39:38.637
<i>AND HE DECIDED TO BET
HIS GIRLFRIEND IN PLACE
OF THE CASHOLA.</i>

39:38.680 --> 39:42.336
AND, WELL,
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY:
"TO THE WINNER GOES THE SPOILS."

39:45.818 --> 39:48.429
[ Brittany ]
ADRIEN, COULD YOU
DO ME A HUGE FAVOR?

39:48.473 --> 39:51.519
WOULD YOU RUN UP TO MY ROOM
AND GET SOME MORE CD's?

39:51.563 --> 39:54.435
WE'RE IN SERIOUS NEED
OF A MOOD CHANGE AROUND HERE.

39:55.784 --> 39:57.525
DEFINITELY.

40:02.791 --> 40:04.706
[ Hiccupping ]

40:12.584 --> 40:15.282
[ Continues Hiccupping,
Laughing ]

40:19.068 --> 40:21.462
I KNOW HOW
TO GET RID OF THOSE.

40:21.506 --> 40:24.596
I GOT A KILLER CURE
-AND IT NEVER FAILS.
-UH-HUH.

40:24.639 --> 40:26.685
NO, REALLY, I AM--
[ Hiccups ]

40:26.728 --> 40:29.514
-UH, FINE.
-HERE. STAND UP.

40:31.167 --> 40:33.692
ALRIGHT.
TURN AROUND.

40:33.735 --> 40:36.477
[ Hiccups ]
ALRIGHT. NOW, I WANT YOU
TO BEND OVER.

40:36.521 --> 40:42.483
-YOU CANNOT BE SERIOUS.
-JUST DO AS THE DOCTOR SAYS.
BEND OVER.

40:45.443 --> 40:49.229
HERE'S A GLASS OF WATER.
NOW, DRINK IT UPSIDE DOWN,
BUT NOT FROM THIS END.

40:49.272 --> 40:52.014
DRINK IT FROM THE FAR END
OVER HERE. DON'T SPILL.

40:54.626 --> 40:57.455
-DID YOU GET SOME?
-MM-HMM.

40:59.892 --> 41:02.547
HMM? YEAH?

41:02.590 --> 41:05.332
SEE?
WHAT DID I TELL YOU?

41:08.074 --> 41:09.641
IT NEVER FAILS.

41:19.607 --> 41:21.870
[ Indistinct ]

41:50.116 --> 41:52.771
NO. WAIT, WAIT.

42:06.262 --> 42:08.221
TOM-- TOM--

42:09.744 --> 42:12.486
-NO. TOM!
-WHAT?

42:12.530 --> 42:17.273
TOM, I SAID... NO!
I SAID NO!

42:17.317 --> 42:19.537
OW! OW!

42:29.372 --> 42:32.245
WHAT?
SHE'S A PRUDE, OKAY?

42:36.641 --> 42:38.294
[ Man ]
COME ON, GUYS.

42:42.255 --> 42:44.692
HEY, I'M GOING
TO TAKE THESE DOWN.

42:48.043 --> 42:50.829
ADRIEN, I'M SORRY
YOU RAN OUT LAST NIGHT.

42:52.439 --> 42:54.920
I DIDN'T RUN. I WALKED.

42:54.963 --> 42:57.487
LOOK, I KNOW TOM
CAN BE AN ASSHOLE,

42:57.531 --> 43:00.752
AND I'M SURE HE DESERVED
THE CRACKED HEAD.

43:02.231 --> 43:05.060
BUT WHAT
DID HE DO EXACTLY?

43:05.104 --> 43:08.107
OH, THE USUAL FRAT BOY
RECREATIONAL DATE RAPE.

43:10.457 --> 43:13.634
YOU COULD'VE TOLD SOMEONE.

43:13.678 --> 43:17.638
WHO IS GOING TO
BELIEVE ME AGAINST HIM?

43:17.682 --> 43:19.379
I WOULD.

43:21.163 --> 43:25.124
I ONLY INVITED HIM
BECAUSE I THOUGHT
YOU WANTED ME TO.

43:25.167 --> 43:28.649
ADRIEN, I'M--
I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.

43:37.092 --> 43:41.706
LOOK, WHY DON'T
WE GET OUT OF HERE?
LET'S JUST GO, RIGHT NOW.

43:41.749 --> 43:43.142
BRIT,
I APPRECIATE THE OFFER,

43:43.185 --> 43:45.927
BUT YOU JUST CAN'T COME
IN HERE AND PULL ME OUT.

43:45.971 --> 43:47.842
I HAVE A JOB.

43:47.886 --> 43:51.150
OKAY, THEN HOW ABOUT TONIGHT?
WE'LL GO DANCING.

43:54.196 --> 43:57.199
IF YOU WANT,
IT CAN BE YOUR TREAT.

44:00.986 --> 44:04.032
OKAY. MY TREAT.

44:04.076 --> 44:05.991
OKAY.

44:29.231 --> 44:31.538
<i>[ Kelly ]
SHE'S JUST
PLAYING WITH YOU.</i>

44:33.583 --> 44:36.674
-EXCUSE ME.
-WAIT. LOOK.

44:36.717 --> 44:40.025
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOUR THING
IS WITH BRITTANY, OKAY?

44:40.068 --> 44:42.375
BUT SHE'S NOT
YOUR FRIEND.

44:42.418 --> 44:45.508
LOOK, KELLY, I DON'T KNOW WHAT <i>
YOUR</i> THING IS WITH BRITTANY,

44:45.552 --> 44:49.861
BUT I DON'T NEED ANYONE
TO TELL ME WHO IS
OR WHO ISN'T MY FRIEND.

44:49.904 --> 44:51.819
YOU DON'T KNOW HER.

44:51.863 --> 44:56.302
LISTEN TO YOURSELF, KELLY. DO
YOU KNOW HOW PATHETIC YOU SOUND?

45:14.015 --> 45:16.931
-YOU BEEN WAITING LONG?
-NO, NOT AT ALL.

45:16.975 --> 45:18.672
LET'S GO.

45:21.675 --> 45:26.114
WELL, TONIGHT'S YOUR NIGHT.
YOUR WISH IS MY COMMAND.

45:26.158 --> 45:29.161
OKAY, WISH NUMBER ONE:
LET'S GET THE HELL
OUT OF HERE.

45:34.688 --> 45:37.778
♪ [ Rock ]

45:37.822 --> 45:39.954
THAT'S A BEAUTIFUL RING.

45:39.998 --> 45:42.391
THANK YOU.

45:42.435 --> 45:45.003
IT WAS MY MOTHER'S.

45:45.046 --> 45:50.791
SHE DIED WHEN I WAS BORN
AND MY FATHER GAVE IT TO ME
ON MY 16th BIRTHDAY.

45:50.835 --> 45:53.751
IT'S SORT OF LIKE MY WAY
OF KEEPING HER WITH ME.

45:58.625 --> 46:01.628
ARE WE LEAVING
-LANG COUNTY?
-UH-HUH.

46:01.671 --> 46:03.325
I'M KIDNAPPING YOU.

46:12.857 --> 46:16.730
WE CAN GO IN HERE AND GET AS
DRUNK AND AS CRAZY AS WE WANT.

46:16.774 --> 46:20.778
AND THE BEST PART IS,
NO ONE KNOWS WHO WE ARE.

46:20.821 --> 46:23.258
♪ [ Rock ]

47:07.955 --> 47:10.436
HEY, LADIES,
HOW'S IT GOING?

47:10.479 --> 47:12.351
YOU GUYS HAVING
A GOOD TIME?

47:12.394 --> 47:16.311
SURE. CAN I GET
YOU TWO A DRINK?

47:16.355 --> 47:17.791
OH, YEAH.

47:17.835 --> 47:19.967
HEY, DUDE.
TWO JUNGLE JUICES.

47:22.274 --> 47:24.885
[ Bartender ]

47:24.929 --> 47:27.235
HERE YOU GO.

47:27.279 --> 47:28.846
WHERE DO YOU GUYS LIVE?

47:28.889 --> 47:31.022
-CHEERS.
-CHEERS.

47:31.065 --> 47:32.937
THANKS FOR THE COCKTAILS.

48:40.656 --> 48:43.964
-THAT GUY WAS SO CUTE.
-YEAH, BUT YOU HAVE
TO BE REALLY CAREFUL.

48:44.008 --> 48:46.749
THERE YOU GUYS ARE.[ Laughing ]

48:55.889 --> 48:57.195
UH, THERE'S AN ACCIDENT.

49:02.940 --> 49:04.463
[ Adrien ]
ISN'T THAT KELLY'S BIKE?

49:06.160 --> 49:07.945
[ Woman ]
ANY UNIT. ANY UNIT. THIS IS...

49:07.988 --> 49:09.772
[ Brittany ]
OH, MY GOD. IT'S KELLY.

49:09.816 --> 49:11.949
-KELLY?
-EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.

49:11.992 --> 49:13.994
I'M SORRY, MA'AM.
YOU HAVE TO KEEP MOVING.

49:14.038 --> 49:18.738
-THAT'S MY FRIEND.
-WHAT HAPPENED?
IS SHE ALRIGHT?

49:18.781 --> 49:21.132
<i>I THINK SO,
BUT YOU HAVE
TO KEEP MOVING.</i>

49:48.768 --> 49:50.161
OH!

49:51.989 --> 49:55.079
YOU KNOW, THE FIRST TIME I SAW
YOU, I THOUGHT YOU WERE...

49:55.122 --> 49:57.646
THAT LITTLE GIRL
RIGHT THERE.

49:57.690 --> 50:00.867
I MEAN, FROM THE RIGHT ANGLE,
YOU TWO COULD ALMOST BE TWINS.

50:00.910 --> 50:03.348
-WHAT'S HER NAME?
-YOU DON'T KNOW?

50:05.698 --> 50:07.569
BRITTANY NEVER
SAID ANYTHING?

50:09.093 --> 50:11.965
THAT'S--
THAT'S SANDRA.

50:12.009 --> 50:14.794
THAT'S BRITTANY'S SISTER.

50:14.837 --> 50:17.753
AND THAT IS BRITTANY.

50:17.797 --> 50:22.541
OR SHOULD I SAY
WAS <i>BRITTANY.</i>

50:22.584 --> 50:24.369
<i>[ Adrien ]
SO SANDRA AND MATT WERE--</i>

50:24.412 --> 50:27.589
YEAH, THEY WERE QUITE
THE COUPLE, ACTUALLY.
HE GOT DUMPED BAD.

50:27.633 --> 50:30.679
YOU COULD HEAR
HIS HEART BREAKING
ALL THE WAY ACROSS THE BAY.

50:30.723 --> 50:33.334
[ Making Clicking Sounds ]

50:33.378 --> 50:36.685
AND I BET YOU KNOW JUST
HOW THAT SOUNDS, DON'T YOU?

50:36.729 --> 50:39.732
-OUCHIE.
-HOW IS KELLY?

50:39.775 --> 50:43.692
SHE... HER LEG'S NOT
IN THE BEST OF SHAPE,

50:43.736 --> 50:46.565
BUT THE DOCTOR SAID
THAT SHE'LL BE ALRIGHT, I GUESS.

50:46.608 --> 50:48.436
GOOD.
GOOD.

51:08.326 --> 51:11.111
<i>[ Tom's Voice ]
NO, NO. YOU SAID
IT WAS GONNA BE EASY.</i>

51:11.155 --> 51:12.721
[ Brittany's Voice ]
IT WAS EASY.

51:12.765 --> 51:15.811
BUT YOU'RE SO LAME RIGHT NOW,
YOU'D SCREW UP A WET DREAM.

51:15.855 --> 51:18.640
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU BLEW THIS.
I HANDED HER TO YOU.

51:18.684 --> 51:20.033
NO.

51:21.687 --> 51:23.689
YOU KNOW, YOUR PARENTS
ARE GONNA BE THRILLED...

51:23.732 --> 51:27.910
WHEN THEY FIND OUT YOU'RE BACK
TO SNORTING YOUR ALLOWANCE
UP YOUR NOSE.

51:27.954 --> 51:30.652
<i>WHAT ELSE DO YOU
WANT ME TO DO, HUH?</i>

51:30.696 --> 51:35.004
I TRIED.
SHE JUST DOESN'T LIKE ME.

51:35.048 --> 51:37.311
YOU TRIED?

51:37.355 --> 51:41.533
YOU TRIED AND YOU FAILED, TOM.
IT'S THE STORY OF YOUR LIFE.

51:57.897 --> 52:00.769
<i>- HEY, MATT.
- HEY.</i>

52:00.813 --> 52:04.121
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT COMING TO TAKE
ME UP ON THAT TENNIS LESSON.

52:04.164 --> 52:07.907
ACTUALLY, I WANTED
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT SANDRA.

52:10.214 --> 52:13.739
THAT PICTURE YOU SAW
OF THE SUMMER'S END PARTY,
THAT WAS TWO YEARS AGO.

52:13.782 --> 52:18.352
THAT WAS
THE LAST TIME WE WENT OUT,
THE LAST TIME I SAW HER EVEN.

52:18.396 --> 52:23.357
SHE TOOK OFF.
SHE EMPTIED HER TRUST FUND
AND JUST TOOK OFF.

52:23.401 --> 52:26.708
ALL THAT TIME I HAD NO IDEA
THAT ALL SHE WANTED TO DO...

52:26.752 --> 52:31.191
WAS TO GET AS FAR AWAY
FROM THIS TOWN, FROM THE CLUB,

52:31.235 --> 52:33.672
FROM ME.

52:33.715 --> 52:36.762
AND I GET
A POSTCARD FROM HER
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE.

52:36.805 --> 52:40.026
FIRST EUROPE AND THEN...
SOUTH AMERICA.

52:45.423 --> 52:48.165
THEN I GOT THIS
TWO WEEKS AGO.

52:48.208 --> 52:51.168
IT BASICALLY SAYS,
"GET ON WITH YOUR LIFE.
I'M NOT COMING BACK."

52:55.824 --> 52:57.826
I CAN'T REALLY BLAME HER.
I MEAN,

52:57.870 --> 53:00.873
I TEACH BORED HOUSEWIVES
HOW TO IMPROVE THEIR BACKHAND.

53:00.916 --> 53:04.224
WHAT'S THAT
-TO A GIRL LIKE SANDRA?
-I GOT AN IDEA.

53:04.268 --> 53:08.402
HOW ABOUT BEFORE YOU START
BEATING UP ON YOURSELF,
WE GET SOMETHING TO EAT?

53:08.446 --> 53:12.276
I MEAN I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,
BUT I'M STARVING.

53:18.020 --> 53:21.067
SO, WHAT ARE YOU IN THE MOOD
FOR? THERE'S ITALIAN UP HERE--

53:21.110 --> 53:22.764
ITALIAN.

53:57.234 --> 53:58.800
THANKS.

54:05.111 --> 54:07.287
<i>WHERE WERE
YOU TONIGHT?</i>

54:11.639 --> 54:14.773
LOOK, I KNOW ABOUT TOM.

54:17.166 --> 54:19.256
I KNOW WHAT YOU DID.

54:21.301 --> 54:25.392
OH, SO, UM, NOW IT'S A CRIME
TO TRY AND HELP A FRIEND?

54:27.089 --> 54:30.658
YOU'RE NOT HELPING. I WASN'T
LOOKING FOR A BOYFRIEND.

54:30.702 --> 54:32.791
RIGHT.

54:32.834 --> 54:35.881
YOU DON'T HAVE TO AS LONG
AS YOU JUST TAKE WHAT'S MINE.

54:38.144 --> 54:41.930
MATT ISN'T YOURS, BRITTANY,
AND I WASN'T TRYING...

54:41.974 --> 54:43.105
TO TAKE HIM.

54:43.149 --> 54:46.457
YOU DON'T GET IT, DO YOU,
ADRIEN?

54:46.500 --> 54:48.502
I SHOWED YOU HOW THINGS
WORKED AROUND HERE...

54:48.546 --> 54:52.158
BECAUSE I SYMPATHIZED
WITH HOW YOU FELT...

54:52.201 --> 54:54.116
BEING THE OUTSIDER.

54:54.160 --> 54:57.032
BUT JUST REMEMBER.

54:57.076 --> 55:00.340
I BROUGHT YOU IN,
AND IF YOU DECIDE
TO FUCK WITH ME,

55:00.384 --> 55:04.649
I CAN JUST
AS EASILY THROW YOU OUT.

55:04.692 --> 55:07.347
AM I SUPPOSED
TO BE SCARED NOW?

55:13.484 --> 55:15.224
I WOULD BE.

55:22.797 --> 55:24.364
THAT'S IT.

55:26.410 --> 55:28.934
BRITTANY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

55:28.977 --> 55:31.719
WELL, HELLO, DR. THOMPSON.

55:31.763 --> 55:34.374
I FIGURED SINCE
I HAD MY ENTIRE SUMMER FREE,

55:34.418 --> 55:36.550
I'D MAKE MYSELF USEFUL,

55:36.594 --> 55:41.033
SO I VOLUNTEER AT THE HOSPITAL
A FEW DAYS A WEEK.

55:41.076 --> 55:44.341
WELL, THAT'S GREAT, BRITTANY.
I AM VERY IMPRESSED.

56:21.116 --> 56:22.727
[ Beeping ]

56:35.392 --> 56:37.959
[ Pager Operator ]
YOUR MESSAGE HAS BEEN SENT.
THANK YOU.

56:43.008 --> 56:47.316
<i>WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?
THE WORST THAT BITCH CAN DO
IS GET YOU FIRED.</i>

56:47.360 --> 56:49.580
YOU DON'T NEED
THIS PLACE, ADRIEN.

56:49.623 --> 56:52.583
ACTUALLY, JO, I DO.

56:52.626 --> 56:56.848
IF I GET FIRED, I GO BACK.

56:56.891 --> 56:59.938
YOU KNOW, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO TELL ME IF YOU DON'T WANT.

56:59.981 --> 57:02.419
ONLY, WHY WERE YOU THERE
IN THE FIRST PLACE?

57:02.462 --> 57:04.421
I MEAN, A HOSPITAL.

57:10.427 --> 57:13.125
WHEN MY PARENTS GOT DIVORCED,

57:13.168 --> 57:16.215
I SORT OF STARTED
ACTING OUT IN SCHOOL.

57:16.258 --> 57:19.740
YOU KNOW, TAKING PILLS,
RUNNING AROUND...

57:19.784 --> 57:23.309
AND A LOT WORSE SHIT
THAN THAT.

57:23.352 --> 57:26.225
SO MY PARENTS SENT ME
TO THE SCHOOL PSYCHOLOGIST.

57:27.879 --> 57:29.968
DR. BECK.

57:32.405 --> 57:35.103
HE WAS JUST ONE OF THOSE PEOPLE
YOU COULD TALK TO.

57:37.584 --> 57:41.588
AND TO ME IT SEEMED
LIKE HE WAS THE ONLY ONE
THAT REALLY CARED.

57:44.069 --> 57:45.984
I DON'T REMEMBER
EXACTLY WHEN,

57:47.768 --> 57:50.031
BUT I STARTED TO FANTASIZE...

57:52.686 --> 57:55.428
SEXUALLY...

57:55.472 --> 57:57.952
ABOUT ME...

57:57.996 --> 58:00.215
AND THE DOCTOR.

58:03.044 --> 58:05.394
AND SO WE STARTED
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

58:08.615 --> 58:10.574
AND THEN...

58:12.663 --> 58:15.230
WE--

58:18.669 --> 58:20.627
<i>WAIT. ADRIEN.</i>

58:23.935 --> 58:25.632
HEY.

58:28.330 --> 58:30.071
YOU MEAN--

58:31.377 --> 58:33.727
YOU MEAN YOU HAD SEX
WITH YOUR DOCTOR?

58:36.730 --> 58:38.340
NO.

58:43.998 --> 58:46.000
BUT IN MY MIND...

58:47.611 --> 58:50.091
I ACTUALLY BELIEVED
THAT WE WERE LOVERS.

58:53.965 --> 58:56.445
AND SUDDENLY,
IT WAS THIS WHOLE THING.

58:58.186 --> 59:01.450
HE HAD TO SHOW HOW I WAS MAKING
THE WHOLE THING UP.

59:03.278 --> 59:05.542
AND I JUST FELT
SO BETRAYED.

59:08.240 --> 59:10.503
SO I WAITED FOR HIM...

59:10.547 --> 59:13.593
ONE DAY AFTER SCHOOL,
JUST TO TALK,

59:13.637 --> 59:15.856
AND HE PRETENDED LIKE
I WASN'T EVEN THERE.

59:17.641 --> 59:19.947
AND I DON'T REMEMBER
IT ALL,

59:19.991 --> 59:24.561
BUT THE NEXT THING I KNEW, I HAD
MY HOCKEY STICK IN MY HAND.

59:26.214 --> 59:28.390
I WAS BRINGING IT DOWN
ON HIS CAR,

59:28.434 --> 59:32.003
AND I WAS SMASHING
HIS WINDSHIELD,
HIS WINDOWS, ANYTHING.

59:37.574 --> 59:42.143
IT TOOK A LONG TIME
IN THE HOSPITAL
FOR ME TO REALIZE THAT...

59:43.667 --> 59:46.234
ALL THAT STUFF
WITH DR. BECK,

59:48.062 --> 59:50.021
IT WASN'T REAL.

59:52.197 --> 59:54.503
IT WAS ALL IN MY HEAD.

59:59.683 --> 01:00:01.380
DO YOU KNOW...

01:00:03.512 --> 01:00:06.864
THAT YOU'RE THE FIRST
REAL PERSON I'VE TOLD?

01:00:17.439 --> 01:00:19.616
I CAN DO IT.
THANK YOU.

01:00:23.097 --> 01:00:26.623
[ Woman ]
HEY, GET THE PLATTER.

01:00:26.666 --> 01:00:27.885
[ Man ]
GOT 'EM.

01:00:27.928 --> 01:00:31.149
WELCOME BACK.
GOOD TO SEE YOU'RE OKAY.

01:00:31.192 --> 01:00:33.630
DO I LOOK OKAY
TO YOU?

01:00:36.545 --> 01:00:40.158
LOOK.
I WANTED TO APOLOGIZE.

01:00:40.201 --> 01:00:42.595
YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT BRITTANY.

01:00:44.902 --> 01:00:48.645
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T KNOW.

01:00:54.259 --> 01:00:57.175
YOU KNOW, SHE WASN'T ALWAYS
THE WAY SHE IS NOW.

01:00:57.218 --> 01:01:00.613
WHEN WE WERE YOUNGER, EVEN WHEN
WE WERE IN HIGH SCHOOL,

01:01:00.657 --> 01:01:02.833
THINGS WERE JUST DIFFERENT.

01:01:02.876 --> 01:01:05.270
SHE WAS DIFFERENT.

01:01:05.313 --> 01:01:08.839
WELL, I'M SURE IT MUST HAVE
BEEN REALLY HARD ON HER
WHEN SANDRA LEFT.

01:01:08.882 --> 01:01:11.711
<i>HARD?
[ Scoffs ]</i>

01:01:11.755 --> 01:01:13.800
YOU REALLY DON'T KNOW
BRIT, DO YOU, ADRIEN?

01:01:15.715 --> 01:01:18.457
SHE HATED SANDRA.

01:01:18.500 --> 01:01:20.111
SANDRA WAS A BITCH.

01:01:20.154 --> 01:01:22.330
I MEAN, SHE WAS A REAL ASSHOLE.

01:01:22.374 --> 01:01:25.420
AND DO YOU KNOW
WHO SHE WAS MEANEST TO?

01:01:25.464 --> 01:01:29.424
<i>BRITTANY.</i>

01:01:29.468 --> 01:01:30.948
YOU KNOW THAT RING
BRITTANY WEARS?

01:01:30.991 --> 01:01:32.993
YEAH, HER MOM'S.

01:01:33.037 --> 01:01:38.085
WHEN THEIR DAD GAVE IT TO BRIT,
SANDRA HAD LOST HER SHIT,
SO SHE STOLE IT.

01:01:38.129 --> 01:01:40.174
TOOK IT RIGHT OFF
BRIT'S FINGER.

01:01:40.218 --> 01:01:43.482
AND HER DAD, HE WAS USELESS.
HE WAS NEVER GONNA CROSS SANDRA.

01:01:43.525 --> 01:01:47.051
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HE DID?
HE HAD A COPY OF THE RING MADE.

01:01:47.094 --> 01:01:50.663
HE GAVE THAT ONE TO BRIT.

01:01:50.707 --> 01:01:54.972
SO, BRITTANY HAS TO WEAR
A COPY OF THE ONLY THING
OF HER MOTHER'S SHE REALLY HAD?

01:01:55.015 --> 01:01:57.714
SHE USED TO
HAVE TO WEAR A COPY.

01:01:59.367 --> 01:02:02.153
LOOK. YOU'RE JUST HERE
FOR THE SUMMER.

01:02:02.196 --> 01:02:04.329
IT'S JUST A JOB FOR YOU.

01:02:06.070 --> 01:02:09.247
FOR SOME OF US, YOU KNOW,
THIS IS OUR LIFE.

01:02:52.290 --> 01:02:54.031
YOU WORK TOO HARD, DOC.

01:02:54.074 --> 01:02:57.686
BRITTANY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:02:57.730 --> 01:03:00.080
<i>EVERYONE'S GONE HOME.</i>

01:03:02.866 --> 01:03:05.477
EVERYONE BUT YOU.

01:03:12.876 --> 01:03:15.182
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE,
BRITTANY?

01:03:15.226 --> 01:03:18.490
DO YOU REMEMBER
THAT TIME AT THE CLUB
WHEN YOU FOUND ME CRYING?

01:03:20.361 --> 01:03:22.537
I WAS CRYING OVER
A BOY.

01:03:29.849 --> 01:03:31.808
IS THAT WHAT
THIS IS ALL ABOUT?

01:03:33.940 --> 01:03:35.899
I'LL NEVER FORGET IT.

01:03:37.596 --> 01:03:40.512
YOU DIDN'T TALK DOWN
TO ME.

01:03:40.555 --> 01:03:42.819
YOU TREATED ME
LIKE A FRIEND.

01:03:45.125 --> 01:03:49.608
BRITTANY, IF THIS IS
ABOUT A BOY--

01:03:49.651 --> 01:03:51.828
IT'S NOT ABOUT A BOY.

01:03:54.918 --> 01:03:56.745
I'M NOT AT ALL
INTERESTED...

01:03:58.138 --> 01:03:59.923
IN BOYS.

01:04:02.795 --> 01:04:04.797
BRITTANY.

01:04:04.841 --> 01:04:09.497
YOU STILL SEE ME AS THAT
16-YEAR-OLD LITTLE GIRL, RIGHT?

01:04:15.982 --> 01:04:17.723
NO.

01:04:17.766 --> 01:04:20.117
BUT I DON'T THINK
YOU WANNA DO THIS.

01:04:21.727 --> 01:04:23.860
WHY?

01:05:40.675 --> 01:05:42.329
<i>HEY, KEL.</i>

01:05:44.462 --> 01:05:46.638
HOW ABOUT
WE GO FOR A SAIL?

01:05:54.211 --> 01:05:56.474
RIGHT NOW?

01:05:56.517 --> 01:06:00.695
I JUST THOUGHT WE BARELY
GET TO SEE EACH OTHER ANYMORE.

01:06:02.654 --> 01:06:04.569
NOT LIKE WE USED TO.

01:06:08.573 --> 01:06:10.749
HERE.

01:06:41.345 --> 01:06:44.000
[ Brittany ]
I KNOW YOU THINK
I'VE BEEN AVOIDING YOU.

01:06:44.043 --> 01:06:46.263
AND YOU'RE RIGHT.
I HAVE.

01:06:46.306 --> 01:06:49.179
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

01:06:49.222 --> 01:06:53.052
IT IS TO ME.
IT'S A VERY BIG DEAL.

01:06:53.096 --> 01:06:55.968
IT'S JUST THE WAY
I FEEL. I--

01:06:58.449 --> 01:07:01.539
I HAVEN'T KNOWN
WHAT TO SAY. I--

01:07:01.582 --> 01:07:04.281
I STILL DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

01:07:04.324 --> 01:07:06.283
SHH.

01:07:09.895 --> 01:07:11.636
IT'S OKAY.

01:08:21.227 --> 01:08:23.447
[ Gasps, Screams ]
OH, MY LEG!

01:08:23.490 --> 01:08:26.624
YOU BITCH!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
BRIT!

01:08:29.104 --> 01:08:32.238
I-I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

01:08:32.282 --> 01:08:34.283
I DIDN'T TELL HER ANYTHING.
I SWEAR.

01:08:34.327 --> 01:08:37.504
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE MY FRIEND.
- PLEASE DON'T!

01:08:39.158 --> 01:08:41.291
[ Crying ]
MY LEG!

01:08:46.078 --> 01:08:47.993
[ Gasping ]

01:08:48.036 --> 01:08:49.515
WAIT!
[ Coughs ]

01:08:52.127 --> 01:08:54.042
- [ Gasping ]
- BYE, KEL.

01:08:54.086 --> 01:08:55.870
<i>I PROMISE!
PLEASE--</i>

01:08:58.220 --> 01:09:00.136
<i>[ Gasping ]</i>

01:09:18.457 --> 01:09:20.852
THIS IS ALL
STILL SO UNREAL.

01:09:22.723 --> 01:09:25.595
KELLY DROWNING,
OF ALL PEOPLE.

01:09:25.639 --> 01:09:28.642
YOU KNOW? DOESN'T IT SEEM
A LITTLE WEIRD TO YOU GUYS?

01:09:32.951 --> 01:09:35.867
WHERE'S TOM?

01:09:35.910 --> 01:09:38.912
UM, I DIDN'T SEE TOM
AT THE FUNERAL.

01:09:38.957 --> 01:09:41.612
MORGAN,
TOM'S BACK IN REHAB.

01:09:41.654 --> 01:09:43.917
[ Greg ]
TOM WENT TO REHAB AGAIN?

01:09:48.184 --> 01:09:50.229
[ Adrien ]
BRIT.

01:09:51.883 --> 01:09:54.189
I AM SO SORRY.

01:10:18.214 --> 01:10:20.868
OH.

01:10:20.912 --> 01:10:22.827
HERE. LET ME HELP YOU
WITH THESE.

01:10:24.524 --> 01:10:26.439
OH, UM,
THOSE AREN'T THAT GOOD.

01:10:26.483 --> 01:10:28.876
I-I GOT BETTER ONES
IN MY ROOM.

01:10:30.878 --> 01:10:34.055
WHERE DID YOU LEARN
-TO PAINT LIKE THIS?
-PRACTICE.

01:10:37.842 --> 01:10:40.975
[ Man ]
BRING YOU ARM BACK, FIRST.
KEEP IT STRAIGHT.

01:10:42.063 --> 01:10:43.456
[ Woman ]
OKAY.

01:10:45.241 --> 01:10:47.504
THAT'S JUST STUFF I FOUND
ON THE GOLF COURSE.

01:10:49.462 --> 01:10:50.681
[ Woman ]
ALRIGHT.

01:10:50.724 --> 01:10:53.249
THESE PEOPLE LOSE MORE
THAN I EVER OWNED.

01:11:11.310 --> 01:11:13.921
[ Woman Laughing ]
MATT!

01:11:13.965 --> 01:11:18.186
[ Man ]
NO, HOW MANY TIMES
HAVE I TOLD YOU THAT.

01:11:18.230 --> 01:11:20.667
[ Chattering ]

01:11:25.019 --> 01:11:28.632
ALRIGHT. NOW LISTEN.
I WANT YOU TO PAY ATTENTION
AND TRY IT AGAIN, OKAY?

01:11:30.938 --> 01:11:33.506
HEY, WHERE YOU GOING?
WE'RE ON KITCHEN IN AN HOUR.

01:11:33.550 --> 01:11:35.987
I MIGHT BE A LITTLE LATE.
COVER FOR ME.

01:11:36.030 --> 01:11:37.815
<i>HEY, WAIT!</i>

01:11:39.686 --> 01:11:41.340
[ Doorbell Rings ]

01:11:46.954 --> 01:11:50.436
HEY, MILENA. I LEFT MY SWEATER
IN BRIT'S ROOM.

01:11:50.480 --> 01:11:54.048
IS IT OKAY
-IF I RUN UP AND GET IT?
-SURE. NO PROBLEM.

01:11:54.092 --> 01:11:57.095
I'LL JUST BE A SEC.
I'LL LET MYSELF OUT.

01:11:57.138 --> 01:12:00.359
- THANKS, MILENA.
- [ Steps Creaking ]

01:15:05.849 --> 01:15:08.678
- OH, I'M SORRY.
WHO ORDERED THE FISH?
- IT'S MY MOTHER'S.

01:15:11.768 --> 01:15:13.770
- THANK YOU.
- I'M SORRY.

01:15:13.813 --> 01:15:15.815
IT'S OKAY.

01:15:17.687 --> 01:15:20.864
[ Woman ]
HENRY IS SO SWEET,
HE WOULDN'T LET ME...

01:15:22.648 --> 01:15:26.173
ADRIEN, GO DOWNSTAIRS
AND BRING UP FOUR TINS
OF CAVIAR.

01:15:26.217 --> 01:15:27.784
OKAY.

01:15:30.264 --> 01:15:32.658
GIVE ME THAT-- <i>YES, SIR.</i>

01:15:32.702 --> 01:15:34.355
[ Pager Beeping ]

01:15:35.705 --> 01:15:37.533
EXCUSE ME.

01:15:45.323 --> 01:15:48.282
-UM, EXCUSE ME.
-OH, SURELY.

01:15:53.853 --> 01:15:56.116
<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>

01:16:10.522 --> 01:16:12.611
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

01:16:26.451 --> 01:16:28.192
ADRIEN?

01:16:29.585 --> 01:16:32.065
[ Brittany ]
YOU DON'T CALL.

01:16:32.109 --> 01:16:34.590
<i>YOU DON'T WRITE.</i>

01:16:36.548 --> 01:16:41.205
BRITTANY. WHAT ARE YOU DOING
HERE?

01:16:41.248 --> 01:16:42.902
DON'T YOU KNOW?

01:16:44.600 --> 01:16:47.690
-BRITTANY, LOOK.
-COME ON.
I KNOW YOU WANT TO.

01:16:47.733 --> 01:16:51.345
NO. BRITTANY,
THAT WAS A MISTAKE.

01:16:51.389 --> 01:16:53.783
IT SHOULD NEVER
HAVE HAPPENED,

01:16:53.826 --> 01:16:55.741
AND IT'S OVER.

01:16:59.049 --> 01:17:01.094
THAT'S TOO BAD.

01:17:23.682 --> 01:17:26.729
<i>COME ON, GUYS.
THIS ISN'T FUNNY.</i>

01:18:09.554 --> 01:18:11.208
[ Woman ]
HERE SHE COMES.

01:18:30.836 --> 01:18:33.230
[ Indistinct Chatter]

01:18:44.502 --> 01:18:48.158
[ Man ]
WHY DON'T YOU GO AHEAD
AND FOLLOW HER DOWN?

01:18:48.201 --> 01:18:50.769
SOME OF THE OTHER PEOPLE
UP HERE ARE...

01:18:50.813 --> 01:18:52.858
[ Woman ]
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
THE SITUATION YOU'RE IN?

01:18:52.902 --> 01:18:57.515
THE JUDGE HAS ORDERED
THAT YOU BE HELD
UNTIL WE CAN DETERMINE...

01:18:57.558 --> 01:18:59.343
WHETHER YOU'RE FIT
TO STAND TRIAL.

01:19:01.606 --> 01:19:06.524
ADRIEN,
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

01:19:06.567 --> 01:19:08.613
I DIDN'T DO THIS.

01:19:08.656 --> 01:19:12.922
THE MURDER WEAPON
WAS FROM A SET OF GOLF CLUBS
IN YOUR POSSESSION.

01:19:12.965 --> 01:19:15.228
YOUR FINGERPRINTS
ARE THE ONLY ONES ON IT.

01:19:15.272 --> 01:19:17.709
I DIDN'T DO THIS.

01:19:17.753 --> 01:19:19.798
FOR GOD SAKES, ADRIEN.

01:19:19.842 --> 01:19:23.976
THEY FOUND TRACES
OF DR. THOMPSON'S SEMEN
ON A DRESS IN YOUR CLOSET.

01:19:26.196 --> 01:19:29.242
SHE WORKED IT ALL OUT
PERFECTLY.

01:19:32.811 --> 01:19:34.682
I'M SO SORRY.

01:19:36.859 --> 01:19:39.078
COME ON, MISS WILLIAMS.

01:19:49.523 --> 01:19:52.657
IT'S TIME FOR YOUR MEDS,
ADRIEN.

01:19:52.700 --> 01:19:56.792
HELLO, ADRIEN.
TOLD YOU YOU'D BE BACK.

01:19:58.750 --> 01:20:01.231
COME ON, TANYA.
YOU KNOW BETTER THAN THAT.

01:20:09.326 --> 01:20:11.632
THANK YOU.

01:20:58.854 --> 01:21:00.856
MATT.

01:21:00.899 --> 01:21:03.032
YOU KNOW WHAT
I'D REALLY LIKE TO DO?

01:21:03.075 --> 01:21:04.511
NO. WHAT?

01:21:04.555 --> 01:21:07.819
AFTER THE SUMMER'S END DANCE...
TOO FAR...

01:21:10.866 --> 01:21:13.912
[ Woman ]
DR. MARTIN,
PLEASE CALL THE OPERATOR.

01:21:13.956 --> 01:21:17.524
DR. MARTIN,
PLEASE CALL THE OPERATOR.

01:21:17.568 --> 01:21:19.657
<i>WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?</i>

01:21:23.574 --> 01:21:25.489
I KNOW YOU DIDN'T KILL
DR. THOMPSON.

01:21:28.231 --> 01:21:31.016
GOING AGAINST
YOUR OWN KIND, BOBBY?

01:21:31.060 --> 01:21:33.453
BRITTANY MIGHT BE
A LOT OF THINGS,

01:21:33.497 --> 01:21:36.108
BUT SHE'S NOT
MY OWN KIND, OKAY?

01:21:40.069 --> 01:21:43.246
I THINK SHE KILLED KELLY.

01:21:43.289 --> 01:21:46.031
MAKES SENSE. THEY KNEW
TOO MUCH ABOUT EACH OTHER.

01:21:48.294 --> 01:21:50.166
LIKE WHERE SANDRA
REALLY IS.

01:21:51.863 --> 01:21:53.517
NOT IN INDIA?

01:21:55.736 --> 01:22:00.480
SHE'S DEAD. THAT'S WHERE
THIS ALL BEGINS, BOBBY.

01:22:00.524 --> 01:22:03.875
WITH SANDRA.

01:22:03.919 --> 01:22:08.097
YOU KNOW THAT BRITTANY
HATED HER. SANDRA WAS
ALWAYS A BITCH TO HER.

01:22:10.751 --> 01:22:13.972
WHAT ABOUT THE POSTCARDS,
ADRIEN?

01:22:14.016 --> 01:22:17.193
THE POSTCARDS
ARE A SCAM.

01:22:17.236 --> 01:22:20.022
I FOUND A STACK OF THEM
IN BRITTANY'S ROOM.

01:22:20.065 --> 01:22:23.199
IT'S A SERVICE.
STAMP COLLECTORS USE IT.

01:22:23.242 --> 01:22:25.984
YOU SEND THEM A POSTCARD
IN AN ENVELOPE,

01:22:26.028 --> 01:22:28.117
AND THEY SEND IT BACK.

01:22:34.732 --> 01:22:37.778
MATT AND BRITTANY ARE GOING TO
THE SUMMER'S END DANCE TOGETHER.

01:22:37.822 --> 01:22:39.780
GUESS SHE GOT
WHAT SHE WANTED.

01:22:39.824 --> 01:22:42.218
IT'S NOT WHAT
BRITTANY WANTED.

01:22:42.261 --> 01:22:44.829
IT'S WHAT SANDRA WANTED.

01:22:46.265 --> 01:22:48.876
SO, WHAT ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO?

01:22:48.920 --> 01:22:52.576
WE DON'T HAVE ANY PROOF.
WE DON'T HAVE ANY CARDS TO PLAY.

01:22:52.619 --> 01:22:56.928
WHAT DO YOU DO WHEN
YOU WANNA STAY IN THE GAME...

01:22:56.972 --> 01:23:00.149
AND YOU HAVE NOTHING
IN YOUR HAND?

01:23:05.197 --> 01:23:06.590
MM-HM.

01:23:12.726 --> 01:23:15.077
-HEY, BRIT.
-HI.

01:23:22.693 --> 01:23:25.261
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

01:24:07.738 --> 01:24:12.438
IT'S COMMON FOR PATIENTS
TO TRANSFER THEIR
EMOTIONAL FEELINGS...

01:24:12.482 --> 01:24:14.484
ONTO THEIR THERAPIST.

01:24:14.527 --> 01:24:16.181
[ Chuckles ]

01:24:17.748 --> 01:24:21.708
NO. YOU SEE,
WE WERE IN LOVE.

01:24:21.752 --> 01:24:23.884
<i>[ Scoffs ]</i>

01:24:23.928 --> 01:24:25.843
I TOLD YOU
YOU WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND.

01:24:28.976 --> 01:24:31.196
WHY DON'T YOU
EXPLAIN IT TO ME?

01:24:34.373 --> 01:24:35.722
OKAY.

01:24:40.162 --> 01:24:42.599
OKAY.

01:24:45.906 --> 01:24:49.562
UM, YOU SEE, YOU'RE ASKING
ME BECAUSE YOU HAVE TO.

01:24:49.606 --> 01:24:53.958
I DON'T REALLY THINK
THAT YOU'RE ASKING ME
'CAUSE YOU'RE MY FRIEND.

01:24:58.876 --> 01:25:02.662
HE TRIED TO STOP LOVING ME.
YOU HAVE TO KNOW.

01:25:04.316 --> 01:25:06.362
HE DIDN'T WANNA HURT ME.

01:25:10.061 --> 01:25:12.368
[ Sighs ]
FINALLY.

01:25:17.677 --> 01:25:20.811
NOW YOU CAN SEE WHY I DON'T
TAKE THOSE HORSE PILLS.

01:25:25.511 --> 01:25:27.209
GOODNIGHT, DOCTOR.

01:25:27.252 --> 01:25:29.602
NIGHT.[ Door Buzzes ]

01:25:44.008 --> 01:25:46.402
DID YOU GET
EVERYTHING?
YEAH.

01:25:50.710 --> 01:25:52.886
♪ [ Dance ]

01:25:52.930 --> 01:25:55.237
♪ CAN'T SEE WHAT I AM SEEIN'

01:25:57.630 --> 01:26:00.111
♪ GATHER I AM ON MY OWN

01:26:02.635 --> 01:26:07.074
♪ I CAN'T EXPLAIN
THE WAY I'M FEELIN' ♪

01:26:07.118 --> 01:26:09.990
♪ WATCHIN' EVERY THING
I KNOW ♪

01:26:12.515 --> 01:26:14.517
♪ I CAN'T BELIEVE
WHAT SHE SAID ♪

01:26:14.560 --> 01:26:16.301
HOW ABOUT A TOAST TO THE SUMMER?

01:26:16.345 --> 01:26:18.782
I'M KINDA GLAD SUMMER'S OVER.

01:26:18.825 --> 01:26:22.220
I CAN'T WAIT TO
GET BACK TO SCHOOL.

01:26:22.264 --> 01:26:23.700
FINE.
TO SUMMER'S END, THEN.

01:26:23.743 --> 01:26:26.442
NO KIDDIN'. TO SUMMER'S END.
I'M DOWN FOR THAT.

01:26:28.183 --> 01:26:30.097
[ Coughs ]

01:26:32.752 --> 01:26:34.754
<i>[ Sheila ]
OH, MY GOD.</i>

01:26:34.798 --> 01:26:38.236
-WHAT DID WE MISS?
-HELLO.
YOU ALL LOOK GREAT.

01:26:41.239 --> 01:26:45.112
HEY, GUYS.
IT'S, UM, PICTURE TIME.

01:26:45.156 --> 01:26:46.853
[ Chattering, Laughter ]

01:26:57.168 --> 01:27:01.216
YOU FOLKS LOOK FANTASTIC.
WHAT I'D LIKE TO DO IS START OFF
WITH TWO PICTURES, OKAY?

01:27:01.259 --> 01:27:04.349
EVERYONE KIND OF SQUEEZE IN.
GET A LITTLE BIT CLOSER THERE.

01:27:05.916 --> 01:27:09.746
<i>ALRIGHT, HERE WE GO.
SMILE, GUYS.</i>

01:27:12.096 --> 01:27:15.447
AND ONE LAST PICTURE.
OKAY, YOU'RE AMONGST FRIENDS.
ENJOY YOURSELVES.

01:27:15.491 --> 01:27:17.797
SMILE. OKAY,
EVERYONE LOOKIN' THIS WAY.

01:27:17.841 --> 01:27:20.322
SMILING. OKAY.
HOLD THAT POSE, PLEASE.

01:27:20.365 --> 01:27:23.020
SHOW MORE TEETH.
MORE TEETH. MORE NOW AND..

01:27:49.873 --> 01:27:52.179
HOW ABOUT A LITTLE
HEMLOCK AND POISON?

01:27:52.223 --> 01:27:53.877
♪ [ Continues ]

01:27:53.920 --> 01:27:57.620
YOU OKAY?
-YOU LOOK A LITTLE PALE.
-OH.

01:27:57.663 --> 01:28:00.492
ME? NO.
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

01:28:05.845 --> 01:28:07.456
OH. THANK YOU.

01:28:11.547 --> 01:28:14.158
- I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU.
- OH.

01:28:14.201 --> 01:28:15.638
OH!

01:28:17.248 --> 01:28:19.555
<i>DON'T LOOK AT ME.
YOU MUST HAVE AN ADMIRER.</i>

01:28:21.296 --> 01:28:23.776
<i>IT WAS THERE
WHEN WE SAT DOWN.</i>

01:28:23.820 --> 01:28:25.256
AREN'T YOU
GONNA OPEN IT?

01:28:25.300 --> 01:28:27.780
YEAH, COME ON. I WANNA SEE
WHAT'S IN THAT THING.

01:28:27.824 --> 01:28:30.087
COME ON, BRIT.
OPEN IT.

01:28:46.756 --> 01:28:49.236
WHO DID THIS?

01:28:49.280 --> 01:28:51.151
WHO DID THIS? <i>WHAT IS IT?</i>

01:28:55.199 --> 01:28:58.594
WHAT?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

01:28:59.899 --> 01:29:02.032
NOTHING.

01:29:02.075 --> 01:29:04.251
I JUST HAVE A HEADACHE.

01:29:39.896 --> 01:29:41.506
[ Phone Rings ]

01:29:44.509 --> 01:29:46.511
[ Rings ]

01:29:48.513 --> 01:29:50.515
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>

01:30:02.397 --> 01:30:04.137
HELLO.

01:30:05.748 --> 01:30:08.490
HELLO?
WHO IS THIS?

01:30:10.143 --> 01:30:12.058
IT'S YOUR SISTER.

01:30:15.148 --> 01:30:17.150
SANDRA?

01:30:17.194 --> 01:30:19.022
<i>[ Hangs Up Phone ]</i>

01:30:53.099 --> 01:30:55.145
[ Grunting ]

01:31:14.860 --> 01:31:16.732
IT'S ONLY A COPY
OF THE RING.

01:31:16.775 --> 01:31:20.170
BUT YOU HAD TO COME,
DIDN'T YOU? JUST TO BE SURE.

01:31:23.652 --> 01:31:29.266
IT MUST HAVE BEEN TOUGH
ALL THOSE YEARS OF "SANDRA THIS"
AND "SANDRA THAT."

01:31:29.309 --> 01:31:32.878
BUT IT WAS YOU.
IT WASN'T SANDRA.

01:31:32.922 --> 01:31:37.666
YOU WERE THE BEAUTIFUL ONE,
THE SPECIAL ONE.

01:31:37.709 --> 01:31:40.059
IF ONLY
SHE WOULD GO AWAY.

01:31:41.539 --> 01:31:43.715
NO. IT WASN'T LIKE THAT.

01:31:45.935 --> 01:31:48.938
YOU DON'T KNOW THE THINGS
THAT SHE DID TO ME.

01:31:50.679 --> 01:31:53.029
[ Chuckles ]
THEY ALL LOVED HER.

01:31:56.162 --> 01:31:58.513
SHE MADE MY LIFE HELL.

01:32:02.212 --> 01:32:04.388
BRITTANY,
YOU NEED HELP.

01:32:07.652 --> 01:32:12.657
- YOU NEED HELP, ADRIEN!
- [ Screams ]

01:32:15.530 --> 01:32:17.749
- [ Dress Material Rips ]
- [ Screams ]

01:32:22.362 --> 01:32:25.191
[ Both Struggling,
Gasping ]

01:32:29.065 --> 01:32:31.763
[ Choking ]

01:32:41.425 --> 01:32:44.036
[ Screams ]

01:32:57.615 --> 01:32:59.443
- [ Screams ]
- WHAT HAPPENED?

01:32:59.486 --> 01:33:01.967
I FOLLOWED HER ONTO
THE GOLF COURSE.
I COULDN'T FIND--

01:33:02.011 --> 01:33:06.624
SANDRA'S OUT THERE!
SANDRA IS BURIED
OUT THERE!

01:33:06.668 --> 01:33:10.541
WE HAVE TO GET YOU
TO A HOSP--
[ Grunts ]

01:33:10.585 --> 01:33:15.633
YOU DON'T ACTUALLY THINK
THAT THEY'RE GONNA BELIEVE YOU,
DO YOU, ADRIEN?

01:33:15.677 --> 01:33:18.462
HUH?[ Panting ]

01:33:21.465 --> 01:33:23.989
[ Sobbing ]

01:33:27.602 --> 01:33:30.648
I MEAN, AFTER ALL,
YOU ARE THE CRAZY ONE, ADRIEN.

01:33:33.346 --> 01:33:35.610
[ Chuckles ]

01:33:46.838 --> 01:33:48.361
ADRIEN?

01:33:52.539 --> 01:33:56.805
ADRIEN, DO YOU REALLY THINK
THAT I KILLED SANDRA
BECAUSE I WAS JEALOUS?

01:34:01.418 --> 01:34:05.901
SEE, I STARTED TAKING
TENNIS LESSONS FROM MATT.

01:34:05.944 --> 01:34:08.904
<i>[ Adrien Grunts,
Sobbing ]</i>

01:34:08.947 --> 01:34:11.341
[ Chuckles ]

01:34:11.384 --> 01:34:14.649
AND SANDRA
GOT ALL CRAZY.

01:34:18.130 --> 01:34:21.699
SO, AFTER THE DANCE
THAT NIGHT...

01:34:21.743 --> 01:34:22.787
[ Metal Clangs ]

01:34:24.920 --> 01:34:27.400
SHE CAME AFTER ME
ON THE STAIRS.

01:34:31.840 --> 01:34:33.580
SO I PUSHED HER.

01:34:36.758 --> 01:34:39.717
I WAS JUST
TRYING TO GET AWAY.

01:34:39.761 --> 01:34:42.938
AND THEN I GOT KELLY
TO HELP ME BURY THE BODY.

01:34:45.723 --> 01:34:51.381
SEE, I COULD GET KELLY
TO DO ANYTHING
I WANTED HER TO DO.

01:34:58.693 --> 01:35:00.520
<i>- [ Brittany Gasps ]
- [ Screams ]</i>

01:35:13.969 --> 01:35:16.319
FUNNY THING HAPPENED
THEN, ADRIEN.

01:35:18.800 --> 01:35:20.932
I STARTED WEARING
SANDRA'S CLOTHES...

01:35:23.805 --> 01:35:26.111
AND PEOPLE NOTICED ME.

01:35:27.852 --> 01:35:32.291
AND I SLOWLY LEARNED
HOW THE WORLD REALLY WORKED.

01:35:34.946 --> 01:35:37.906
I WAS JUST
TRYING TO SHOW YOU,

01:35:37.949 --> 01:35:40.299
<i>AND THEN
YOU TURNED ON ME.</i>

01:35:51.963 --> 01:35:54.139
[ Screams ]

01:36:11.243 --> 01:36:13.855
<i>[ Metal Scraping ]</i>

01:36:30.654 --> 01:36:32.699
[ Brittany Yells ]

01:37:19.050 --> 01:37:20.617
[ Panting ]

01:37:21.270 --> 01:37:23.576
HELP ME!

01:37:23.620 --> 01:37:29.539
SOMEBODY!
PLEASE, HELP--

01:37:29.582 --> 01:37:32.934
I'M SORRY. THIS MEANS
WE'RE NOT FRIENDS ANYMORE,
HUH, ADRIEN?

01:37:32.977 --> 01:37:34.283
[ Screaming ]

01:37:34.326 --> 01:37:35.632
HELP!

01:37:38.635 --> 01:37:40.811
YOU STUPID BITCH![ Screams ]

01:38:01.919 --> 01:38:05.531
-WHAT IS IT?
-YOU GUYS, HELP ME!

01:38:05.575 --> 01:38:09.013
- [ Coughing ] <i>
- SHE TRIED TO KILL ME.
SHE'S CRAZY.</i>

01:38:09.057 --> 01:38:11.886
<i>COME ON, YOU GUYS.
DO SOMETHING.
SHE KILLED DR. THOMPSON.</i>

01:38:11.929 --> 01:38:15.759
<i>YOU KILLED HIM!
YOU KILLED DR. THOMPSON!</i>

01:38:15.802 --> 01:38:18.893
JUST LIKE YOU KILLED SANDRA,
YOUR OWN FLESH AND BLOOD...

01:38:18.936 --> 01:38:21.504
AND BURIED HER
ON THE GOLF COURSE!

01:38:21.547 --> 01:38:23.375
- YOU KILLED KELLY!
YOU KILLED KELLY.
- [ Coughing ]

01:38:33.124 --> 01:38:38.390
NO, I DIDN'T! LOOK.
SHE'S THE CRAZY ONE HERE, NOT
ME!

01:38:38.434 --> 01:38:39.696
OH, MY GOD.

01:38:39.739 --> 01:38:43.091
PLEASE!

01:38:50.750 --> 01:38:52.970
GET ME OUT OF HERE.
[ Groans ]

01:39:05.722 --> 01:39:08.029
WHAT?

01:39:08.072 --> 01:39:10.248
WHAT ARE YOU ALL
STARING AT?

01:39:10.292 --> 01:39:12.424
YOU THINK YOU KNOW ME?

01:39:12.468 --> 01:39:16.820
YOU THINK I'M THE BEAUTIFUL,
LITTLE RICH GIRL WHO HAS TO
HAVE EVERYTHING HER WAY?

01:39:16.863 --> 01:39:21.912
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW WHO I WAS
UNTIL SANDRA DISAPPEARED
AND I TOOK HER PLACE.

01:39:21.956 --> 01:39:24.871
[ Giggles ]
YOU MADE ME THIS WAY.

